-- ON THE MOVE-Raymond James hires Wells Fargo adviser in Massachusetts
-- 
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 05:27PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 27 (Reuters) - Raymond James & Associates, the branch-based arm of the brokerage and investment firm Raymond James Financial <RJF.N>, said on Wednesday it hired broker Bob Clayson away from Wells Fargo Advisors <WFC.N>.

Clayson, who officially joined Raymond James in June, managed $115 million in client assets at Wells Fargo.  A 43-year-old industry veteran, Clayson spent a decade working at Wells. He has also worked at Morgan Stanley and Bear Stearns.  He is joined by senior registered client service associate Carolyne Wabuyele. The two are based at the firm's Wellesley Hills, Massachusetts office.